Very nice spot.  Very inexpensive and a real old school eating house feel, in a nondescript suburban neighborhood.  There is a stall inside with pre cooked foods but I ate from the kitchen of the Delicious Eating House itself.  Thai style crispy chicken was awesome; light, sweet, flavorful, fragrant and it had a delightfully lingering spicy heat that crept up on you after a time.  Kangkong in spicy sambal and green beans with dried prawn crumbles were winners.  Die die must try.
